<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-07-15T03:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-07-15T03:00:00-05:00" n="48" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d48">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A4/20: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-07-15T09:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">July 15,
                                        1921—9 a.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received 1:47
                            p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>586. Your 398, July 13, 6 p.m. The British Government confirm with
                            satisfaction their acceptance conveyed orally on July 10th through the
                            United States Ambassador of the invitation of the <pb facs="0158" n="34" xml:id="pg_34"/> United States Government to participate in a
                            conference of the five Powers, United States, Great Britain, France,
                            Italy and Japan, to be held at mutual convenience in Washington for the
                            purpose of considering the question of limitation of armaments.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>